desc.html: This is a map to accompany the article about Axstane Hundred in Kent, a longstanding traditional subdivision of that county. Author - Created by myself. The map is a simple graphical representation of the parishes of the Hundred listed in the History and Topographical Survey of the County of Kent: Volume 1, author:Edward Hasted, publ. 1797. The boundaries are redrawn from the 19th century 1 inch to 1 mile Ordnance survey map, which shows parish boundaries. These are available in printed form and can be viewed at online at Visionofbritain.org.uk and elsewhere
